        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 10 at 5:48PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 548 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Dayton, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Riceville, Charleston, Calhoun, Hillsview, Big Spring, Dayton,
Dentville, and Athens.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
east Tennessee.</instruction>
